&lt;h1 id="american-fall"&gt;American Fall&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oct 18 2016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a sequel. Read [American Spring](American Spring) first.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We conclude that the concentration of wealth is natural and inevitable, and is periodically alleviated by violent or peaceable partial redistribution. In this view all economic history is the slow heartbeat of the social organism, a vast systole and diastole of concentrating wealth and compulsive recirculation.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>American Spring</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/american-spring/</link><pubDate>Fri, 15 Jan 2016 09:21:40 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/american-spring/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/naval/zh/american-spring.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
